-- Aeroflot, Gazprom, Polymetal, VSMPO May Be Active: Russian Equity Preview
-- Ilya Khrennikov
-- 2010-06-25T02:00:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-25/aeroflot-gazprom-polymetal-vsmpo-may-be-active-russian-equity-preview.html

          
          
             The following companies may be
active in Russian trading. Stock symbols are in parentheses and
share prices are from the previous close of trading in Moscow.  
 The Micex Index of 30 stocks fell 1.1 percent to 1,363.15
at the close in Moscow. The dollar-denominated RTS Index
declined 1.1 percent to 1,402.97.  
 OAO Aeroflot  (AFLT RX): Boeing Co. will sell more than $3
billion worth of its 737 airliners to Russia, under a contract
signed during Russian President  Dmitry Medvedev ’s visit to
Washington. Aeroflot, Russia’s largest air carrier, rose 0.3
percent to 60.77 rubles.  
 OAO Gazprom  (GAZP RX): The world’s biggest natural-gas
producer holds an annual shareholders meeting, where Chief
Executive Officer  Alexei Miller  is scheduled to speak on the
company’s plans. Gazprom fell 2.1 percent to 154.82 rubles.  
 OAO Polymetal  (PMTL RX): Gold futures rose the most in a
week on speculation that the Federal Reserve will keep U.S.
borrowing costs low for an extended period, weakening the
dollar. Polymetal, Russia’s gold and silver producer, dropped
3.9 percent to 403.46 rubles.  
 OAO VSMPO-Avisma  (VSMO RX): Aircraft maker Boeing Co.
signed a five-year contract extension to buy titanium products
from Russia’s VSMPO-Avisma. VSMPO, the world’s biggest titanium
maker, declined 0.4 percent to 3,087.35 rubles.  
